# RECAST 01 - Nucleus Maturity Audit Report - 2026-06-03

## Scope

Workspace root: `/opt/Axodus`

Audited nuclei:

- ACS
- Academy
- AxodusAPP
- BBA-Agency
- Business
- Core
- Defi
- Dex
- Documentation
- Governance
- Lottery
- Marketplace
- Mining
- Trading
- Global Docs / Instructions

## Objective

Assign a conservative L0-L7 baseline maturity level to each Axodus nucleus and create a portfolio register with confidence, blockers, portfolio state, next target, and next recommended work.

This was an audit/documentation execution. It did not implement fixes.

## Framework Used

The audit used `.instructions/NUCLEUS_MATURITY_FRAMEWORK.md`.

RECAST 00 artifacts were missing at audit start, so RECAST 01 recorded the active framework under the coordinator-approved execution gate in the request.

## BUB Agents Used

Five bounded read-only BUB audit agents were started:

- Core / Global Docs / Documentation
- Governance / AxodusAPP
- Dex / Defi / Trading
- Marketplace / Academy / BBA-Agency
- Mining / Business / Lottery / ACS

All five audit slices returned before final validation and were incorporated: Core / Global Docs / Documentation, Governance / AxodusAPP, Dex / Defi / Trading, Marketplace / Academy / BBA-Agency, and Mining / Business / Lottery / ACS.

## Evidence Sources

- root `.instructions` files;
- nucleus `.instructions` directories;
- nucleus `STATUS.md`, `TASKS.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, `WORKFLOW.md`, `SECURITY.md`, and `BUB_AGENTS.md` presence;
- report inventories under `.instructions/reports`;
- package script discovery from `package.json`, README files, and instruction docs;
- safe git summaries with `git status --short --branch -uno`;
- BBA ignore check for `.instructions/BUB_AGENTS.md`;
- returned BUB audit slice for ACS, Business, Lottery, and Mining.

No builds, tests, installs, services, runtime commands, deployments, package changes, production configs, secrets, settlement, trading, swaps, payouts, wallet signing, or on-chain writes were executed.

