- Recommended next portfolio sprint: PORTFOLIO SPRINT 01 - Balanced Roadmap & Sprint Allocation.

## Per-Nucleus Notes

### ACS

ACS is classified L5 because instruction evidence includes API contracts, policy matrices, security models, readiness review evidence, and AxodusAPP visibility. It remains HOLD because real runtime mutation, trading, Hummingbot control, treasury movement, secrets, and bypassing Governance/Core boundaries are forbidden.

### Academy

Academy is classified L4 from instructions, AxodusAPP route/module visibility, mock PoK validation, local JSON persistence, in-memory test adapter, OpenAPI, Fastify routes, repository contracts, and contract read model evidence. It lacks `STATUS.md`, and production certification, rewards, credentialing, contract writes, minting, transfers, withdrawals, and financial-value semantics remain gated.

### AxodusAPP

AxodusAPP is classified L4. `STATUS.md` records recovered frontend validation, the app shell, tenant runtime, module visibility, and local/mock/read-only Governance integration. Real-data integration and execution flows remain blocked.

### BBA-Agency

BBA-Agency is classified L2. It has normalized instructions and `STATUS.md`, older mock-mode permission/test evidence, Zod schemas, TypeScript contracts, and read-only prototype route evidence. `git check-ignore -v .instructions/BUB_AGENTS.md` produced no ignore match, so instructions versioning appears resolved. Current validation remains undefined/unexecuted.

### Business

Business is classified L4 from mock/read-only runtime contracts, repository contract docs, ACS bridge visibility, non-execution flags, and AxodusAPP `/business/*` visibility. Persistence and real approvals remain blocked.

### Core

Core is classified L5. `STATUS.md` records pre-RC hardening, conformance, consumer certification, public API checks, registry/docs indexes, and product profiles. Core is not an execution authority and remains pre-RC.

### Defi

Defi is classified L4 from Phase 2 local/dev workflow foundation, read-only APIs, contracts, OpenAPI/mock package, simulated receipts, proposal-draft-only flows, AxodusAPP mocks, and Phase 3 planning docs. Phase 3 implementation, custody, adapters, staking, rebalancing, validator scoring, production oracle/accounting/reconciliation, and fund movement remain blocked.

### Dex

Dex is classified L3 overall. Narrow registry and route metadata subtracks have L5-style contract evidence, but the full DEX product remains mock/local and non-production. Linked forks, token-list repos, routing, swaps, settlement, and treasury execution remain blocked.

### Documentation

Documentation is classified L3. It has standards and guardrails plus prior `docs:build` and local VitePress surface evidence, but lacks nucleus `STATUS.md`, `ROADMAP.md`, `WORKFLOW.md`, and `SECURITY.md`.

### Governance

Governance is classified L5 and marked HOLD / PILOT COMPLETE / BACKLOG CONTROLLED. Narrow local/read-only areas may be partial L6, but the overall portfolio state remains HOLD. No Governance API transport implementation, HTTP routes/controllers, real DB, AxodusAPP real client, executor, treasury, or on-chain writes are approved.

Governance API Transport Track: BACKLOG CONTROLLED.

### Lottery

Lottery is classified L2 from mock/read-only API and frontend fallback evidence plus known validation commands. It lacks `STATUS.md`; compliance, VRF/randomness, prize, payout, treasury, contracts, and audit design are blocked.

### Marketplace

Marketplace is classified L5 from AxodusAPP Marketplace visibility, local JSON/API persistence, frontend mock fallback, DTO/repository/controller interfaces, and broad `/api/marketplace` endpoint contracts. It lacks `STATUS.md`; wallet transactions, blockchain writes, external payment gateways, treasury movement, production LayerZero/bridge messages, contract settlement, minting, value-bearing asset transfer, and payments remain gated.

### Mining

Mining is classified L3 from read-only mock API evidence, package commands/tests, non-executing provider flags, contracts, and AxodusAPP `/mining/*` visibility. Provider custody, accounting, compliance, treasury, payout, and real provider execution are blocked.

### Trading

Trading is classified L4 from local Postgres E2E recovery documentation, documented `npm run trading:local:e2e -- --cleanup --json` PASS evidence, local/paper-only boundaries, Trading Core contracts/APIs, product-surface routing through other nuclei, and credential vault planning. It is HOLD because live trading, real exchange keys, withdrawals, production Credential Vault/KMS/HSM, production DB, treasury actions, and vendor ownership risks remain blocked.

### Global Docs / Instructions

Global Docs / Instructions is classified L1. RECAST 01 created the maturity framework and portfolio docs, but `/opt/Axodus` is not a Git repository and RECAST 00 artifacts were missing.

